      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ICRF

        public static final EphemerisElement.FRAME ICRF
        Value ID for ICRF reference frame. An offset is conveniently applied to transform from mean dynamical frame. This correction is convenient for apparent true positions in the sky refered to the ICRS system. If you are in doubt, DO NOT SELECT ICRF.

      • DYNAMICAL_EQUINOX_J2000

        public static final EphemerisElement.FRAME DYNAMICAL_EQUINOX_J2000
        Value ID for dynamical equinox of J2000 frame, adequate (in combination with other options like apparent positions and equinox of date) to obtain ephemerides for the true equator and equinox of date. The difference with ICRF is about 0.02". If you are in doubt, DO SELECT THIS.

      • FK5

        public static final EphemerisElement.FRAME FK5
        ID for selecting old FK5 frame in output positions. Select this in combination with astrometric positions (and a given epoch, like J2000) to obtain planetary positions that can be compared to stellar catalogs in FK5 frame.

      • FK4

        public static final EphemerisElement.FRAME FK4
        ID for selecting very old FK4 frame in output positions.
